title: Wall Street's 'meh' response to tech IPOs shows Silicon Valley's valuation problem
description: Investors are unenthusiastic about the IPOs from Arm, Instacart and Klaviyo, even after a 21-month drought in tech offerings

title: House recesses after Defense bill, government funding plan implode
description: House Speaker Kevin McCarthy sent members home for the weekend after a bill to fund the Pentagon and a plan to vote on government funding both imploded.

title: Saudi crown prince says he will keep 'sportswashing' as criticism of the practice grows
description: Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman embraced 'sportswashing' criticism in a Fox News interview, saying the practice has led to a growth of GDP.

title: Microsoft to sell AI assistant software to biggest clients starting Nov. 1
description: Some small businesses have begun testing Microsoft 365 Copilot, which can help corporate workers compose documents and find information from email messages.

title: JPMorgan legal fees in Jeffrey Epstein sex traffic cases near $14 million, former exec reveals
description: JPMorgan Chase has racked up $13.8 million in legal fees defending itself against allegations of facilitating Jeffrey Epstein's sex trafficking operation.

title: Here’s everything Microsoft announced at its Surface and Copilot event in New York
description: Microsoft announced fresh AI capabilities for advertisers, along with new Surface PCs and a Windows update.

title: Where key issues stand as UAW closes in on extended strikes against GM, Ford and Stellantis
description: The UAW and General Motors, Ford Motor and Stellantis are all holding their ground on demands, and it appears likely the union will strike additional plants.

title: Ukraine leader Zelenskyy to meet with Biden, Congress as some Republicans sour on support
description: Biden will welcome Zelenskyy to the White House on Thursday as the embattled leader seeks to shore up additional support for his war-torn country.

title: Rupert Murdoch steps down as chairman of Fox and News Corp
description: Murdoch's departure comes as his media empire, which includes The Wall Street Journal and Fox News, gears up for the 2024 election.

title: Cisco acquiring cybersecurity company Splunk in cash deal worth $28 billion
description: Cisco said it was acquiring cybersecurity software company Splunk for $157 a share in a cash deal worth about $28 billion.

title: Turkey's central bank hikes interest rate to 30%
description: The move is a 500-basis point jump from the month prior, as Ankara continues to battle double-digit inflation.

title: Bank of England ends run of 14 straight interest rate hikes after cooler-than-expected inflation
description: The Bank of England on Thursday ended a run of 14 straight interest rate hikes after new data showed inflation is now running below expectations.

title: Saudi crown prince says Israel diplomatic normalization closer every day
description: Prince Mohammed dismissed reports that the two countries had suspended talks.

title: India suspends visa services in Canada as diplomatic crisis escalates
description: Canada is currently investigating "credible allegations" that New Delhi orchestrated the extra-judicial slaying of Sikh separatist Hardeep Singh Nijjar in June.

title: Sweden's central bank raises rates to 4%, in line with expectations
description: Sweden's central bank hiked interest rates for the eighth consecutive time Thursday, as the country continues to battle high inflation.

title: Shares of YG tumble over 13% after report three Blackpink members will not renew contracts
description: Members Jisoo, Jennie and Lisa will reportedly sign with other labels, while Rosé will renew her contract with YG.

title: Swiss National Bank holds rates unchanged, ending hike streak
description: The Swiss National Bank kept interest rates unchanged at its quarterly monetary policy meeting on Thursday.

title: One of Ukraine's strongest allies says it will no longer supply Kyiv with weapons
description: A recent dispute over Ukraine's agricultural exports has threatened to break the alliance with its neighbors.

title: AI is all the rage now, but the gaming industry may not be ready to adopt it just yet
description: Some of the biggest game developers in Japan say trends like generative AI and virtual reality/augmented reality headsets for game development may not be ready yet.

title: CNBC Daily Open: Try to look on the bright side of higher-for-longer rates
description: Try to see the Federal Reserve's hawkish dot plot from a glass-half-full perspective. That’s what Fed Chair Jerome Powell seems to be suggesting, at least.

title: How can you tell if a job is right for you? Ask these 'overt questions,' organizational psychologist says
description: "Interview processes aren't set up for us to really get to know each other on a deep level," said Andre Martin. "You have to be an expert question asker."

title: Chinese EV maker Nio releases a smartphone it expects at least half of its users to buy
description: Chinese electric car brand Nio released an Android smartphone on Thursday. CEO William Li spoke with CNBC in an exclusive interview ahead of the launch.

title: These are the 50 best hotels in the world
description: The best hotel in the world is Passlacqua, an 18th century villa on the edge of Italy's Lake Como, according to the 50 Best organization's inaugural ranking.

title: Hollywood studios, writers near agreement to end strike, hope to finalize deal Thursday, sources say
description: While optimistic, the people noted, however, that if a deal is not reached the strike could last through the end of the year.

title: CNBC Daily Open: Try to see the bright side of higher-for-longer rates
description: Try to see the Federal Reserve's hawkish dot plot from a glass-half-full perspective. That’s what Fed Chair Jerome Powell seems to be suggesting, at least.
